00:06:34.630 --> 00:06:40.040
I used to always worry about what others thought of me.

00:06:42.580 --> 00:06:43.500
But...

00:06:44.790 --> 00:06:47.580
Before we started shooting, the director told me...

00:06:48.330 --> 00:06:52.250
For this film, Hayama-san, please unleash
all of my own emotions,

00:06:52.380 --> 00:06:53.960
and just let them all out on set.

00:06:54.750 --> 00:06:57.790
If it were just about playing a character,
I think I'd be fine.

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:04.250
But to unleash my own emotions...

00:07:06.920 --> 00:07:08.790
What does that even mean?

00:07:10.540 --> 00:07:13.960
Your own emotions, huh?

00:07:14.540 --> 00:07:17.920
That might be a tough one for you, Hayama.

00:07:20.040 --> 00:07:21.880
Hey, what about Shirasaki?

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.960
He's the type who just lays
all his emotions bare, isn't he?

00:07:25.080 --> 00:07:26.920
Why don't you learn from him?

00:07:28.880 --> 00:07:30.880
You should talk it over with Shirasaki.

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:34.080
